sw@debian:~/sandbox$ </fo:block></fo:block><fo:block space-before.minimum="0.1em" space-before.optimum="0.1em" space-before.maximum="0.1em" space-after.optimum="1em" space-after.minimum="0.8em" space-after.maximum="1.2em">Da dieses Szenario – dass man einfach nur einen Wert identisch
      zurückgeben will – so häufig auftritt, gibt es dafür schon eine
      vorgefertigte Getter-Methode mit dem Namen
      <fo:inline font-family="DejaVuSansMono">attr_reader</fo:inline>, die wie folgt im Programm
      <fo:inline font-family="DejaVuSansMono">raum.rb</fo:inline> angewendet werden würde:<fo:block id="id2547263" text-align="start" wrap-option="wrap" hyphenation-character="\" space-before.minimum="0.8em" space-before.optimum="1em" space-before.maximum="1.2em" space-after.minimum="0.8em" space-after.optimum="1em" space-after.maximum="1.2em" hyphenate="true" white-space-collapse="false" white-space-treatment="preserve" linefeed-treatment="preserve" font-family="DejaVuSansMono" background-color="#FBFEDF" color="black" padding-left="12pt" padding-right="12pt" padding-top="6pt" padding-bottom="6pt" margin-left="0pc">class Raum
  def initialize
    @tueren  = 1
    @fenster = 1
  end
  
  <fo:inline font-weight="bold">attr_reader :tueren, :fenster</fo:inline>   # die Namen werden als Symbol angegeben
end

wohnzimmer = Raum.new

puts wohnzimmer.tueren
puts wohnzimmer.fenster
</fo:block></fo:block><fo:block id="id2547276" color="#000033" background-color="#C1FDF4" space-before.optimum="1em" space-before.minimum="0.8em" space-before.maximum="1.2em" space-after.optimum="1em" space-after.minimum="0.8em" space-after.maximum="1em" padding-bottom="12pt" padding-top="12pt" padding-right="12pt" padding-left="12pt" margin-left="0pc"><fo:list-block provisional-distance-between-starts="36pt + 18pt" provisional-label-separation="18pt"><fo:list-item><fo:list-item-label end-indent="label-end()"><fo:block><fo:external-graphic width="auto" height="auto" content-width="36pt" src="url(docbook-xsl-ns-1.75.2/images/note.svg)"/></fo:block></fo:list-item-label><fo:list-item-body start-indent="body-start()"><fo:block font-size="13pt" color="#000033" font-weight="bold" hyphenate="true" keep-with-next.within-column="always">Anmerkung</fo:block><fo:block><fo:block space-before.minimum="0.1em" space-before.optimum="0.1em" space-before.maximum="0.1em" space-after.optimum="1em" space-after.minimum="0.8em" space-after.maximum="1.2em"><fo:inline font-family="DejaVuSansMono">attr_reader</fo:inline> ist ein gutes Beispiel für
        Meta-Programmierung in Ruby. Sie werden gerade bei der Arbeit mit
        Rails immer wieder auf Meta-Programmierung stoßen und sich über die
        Automagie freuen.</fo:block></fo:block></fo:list-item-body></fo:list-item></fo:list-block></fo:block><fo:block space-before.minimum="0.1em" space-before.optimum="0.1em" space-before.maximum="0.1em" space-after.optimum="1em" space-after.minimum="0.8em" space-after.maximum="1.2em">Wenn man von Außen die Anzahl der Türen oder Fenster verändern
      will, so braucht man dafür eine <fo:inline>„Setter“</fo:inline>-Methode. Die kann
      wie folgt realisiert werden:<fo:block id="id2547298" text-align="start" wrap-option="wrap" hyphenation-character="\" space-before.minimum="0.8em" space-before.optimum="1em" space-before.maximum="1.2em" space-after.minimum="0.8em" space-after.optimum="1em" space-after.maximum="1.2em" hyphenate="true" white-space-collapse="false" white-space-treatment="preserve" linefeed-treatment="preserve" font-family="DejaVuSansMono" background-color="#FBFEDF" color="black" padding-left="12pt" padding-right="12pt" padding-top="6pt" padding-bottom="6pt" margin-left="0pc">class Raum
  def initialize
    @tueren  = 1
    @fenster = 1
  end
  
  attr_reader :tueren, :fenster
  
  <fo:inline font-weight="bold">def tueren=(value)</fo:inline>       # Setter fuer tueren
    <fo:inline font-weight="bold">@tueren = value</fo:inline>
  <fo:inline font-weight="bold">end</fo:inline>
  
  <fo:inline font-weight="bold">def fenster=(value)</fo:inline>      # Setter fuer fenster
    <fo:inline font-weight="bold">@fenster = value</fo:inline>
  <fo:inline font-weight="bold">end</fo:inline>
end

wohnzimmer = Raum.new

puts wohnzimmer.tueren
puts wohnzimmer.fenster

wohnzimmer.fenster = 2     # fenster wird neu gesetzt

puts wohnzimmer.fenster
</fo:block></fo:block><fo:block space-before.minimum="0.1em" space-before.optimum="0.1em" space-before.maximum="0.1em" space-after.optimum="1em" space-after.minimum="0.8em" space-after.maximum="1.2em">Die entsprechende Ausgabe dazu:<fo:block id="id2547346" text-align="start" wrap-option="wrap" hyphenation-character="\" space-before.minimum="0.8em" space-before.optimum="1em" space-before.maximum="1.2em" space-after.minimum="0.8em" space-after.optimum="1em" space-after.maximum="1.2em" hyphenate="true" white-space-collapse="false" white-space-treatment="preserve" linefeed-treatment="preserve" font-family="DejaVuSansMono" background-color="#FBFEDF" color="black" padding-left="12pt" padding-right="12pt" padding-top="6pt" padding-bottom="6pt" margin-left="0pc">sw@debian:~/sandbox$ <fo:inline font-weight="bold">ruby raum.rb</fo:inline>
1
1
2
sw@debian:~/sandbox$ </fo:block></fo:block><fo:block space-before.minimum="0.1em" space-before.optimum="0.1em" space-before.maximum="0.1em" space-after.optimum="1em" space-after.minimum="0.8em" space-after.maximum="1.2em">Sie können es sich wahrscheinlich schon denken: Natürlich gibt es
      dazu auch einen vorgefertigen und kürzeren Weg. Mit der Methode
      <fo:inline font-family="DejaVuSansMono">attr_writer</fo:inline> können Sie den Code von
      <fo:inline font-family="DejaVuSansMono">raum.rb</fo:inline> weiter vereinfachen:<fo:block id="id2547367" text-align="start" wrap-option="wrap" hyphenation-character="\" space-before.minimum="0.8em" space-before.optimum="1em" space-before.maximum="1.2em" space-after.minimum="0.8em" space-after.optimum="1em" space-after.maximum="1.2em" hyphenate="true" white-space-collapse="false" white-space-treatment="preserve" linefeed-treatment="preserve" font-family="DejaVuSansMono" background-color="#FBFEDF" color="black" padding-left="12pt" padding-right="12pt" padding-top="6pt" padding-bottom="6pt" margin-left="0pc">class Raum
  def initialize
    @tueren  = 1
    @fenster = 1
  end
  
  attr_reader :tueren, :fenster
  
  <fo:inline font-weight="bold">attr_writer :tueren, :fenster</fo:inline>
end

wohnzimmer = Raum.new

puts wohnzimmer.tueren
puts wohnzimmer.fenster

wohnzimmer.fenster = 2

puts wohnzimmer.fenster
</fo:block></fo:block><fo:block space-before.minimum="0.1em" space-before.optimum="0.1em" space-before.maximum="0.1em" space-after.optimum="1em" space-after.minimum="0.8em" space-after.maximum="1.2em">Und (wer hätte das gedacht!) es gibt auch eine Methode
      <fo:inline font-family="DejaVuSansMono">attr_accessor</fo:inline>, die Getter und Setter
      kombiniert. Der Code für <fo:inline font-family="DejaVuSansMono">raum.rb</fo:inline> sähe dann so
      aus:<fo:block id="id2547393" text-align="start" wrap-option="wrap" hyphenation-character="\" space-before.minimum="0.8em" space-before.optimum="1em" space-before.maximum="1.2em" space-after.minimum="0.8em" space-after.optimum="1em" space-after.maximum="1.2em" hyphenate="true" white-space-collapse="false" white-space-treatment="preserve" linefeed-treatment="preserve" font-family="DejaVuSansMono" background-color="#FBFEDF" color="black" padding-left="12pt" padding-right="12pt" padding-top="6pt" padding-bottom="6pt" margin-left="0pc">class Raum
  def initialize
    @tueren  = 1
    @fenster = 1
  end
  
  <fo:inline font-weight="bold">attr_accessor :tueren, :fenster</fo:inline>
end

wohnzimmer = Raum.new

puts wohnzimmer.tueren
puts wohnzimmer.fenster

wohnzimmer.fenster = 2

puts wohnzimmer.fenster
</fo:block></fo:block></fo:block><fo:block id="id2547407"><fo:block><fo:block><fo:block margin-left="0pc" font-family="MetaPlusBold,Symbol,ZapfDingbats" keep-together.within-column="always"><fo:block keep-with-next.within-column="always"><fo:block font-family="MetaPlusBold" font-weight="bold" keep-with-next.within-column="always" space-before.minimum="1.8em" space-before.optimum="2.0em" space-before.maximum="2.2em" space-after.minimum="0.1em" space-after.optimum="0.1em" space-after.maximum="0.1em" text-align="left" start-indent="0pc"><fo:marker marker-class-name="section.head.marker">Mitgelieferte Methoden bei String</fo:marker><fo:block color="#000033" font-size="12.6pt">2.7.2. Mitgelieferte Methoden bei String</fo:block></fo:block></fo:block></fo:block></fo:block></fo:block><fo:block space-before.minimum="0.1em" space-before.optimum="0.1em" space-before.maximum="0.1em" space-after.optimum="1em" space-after.minimum="0.8em" space-after.maximum="1.2em">Die meisten Klassen kommen von Hause aus schon mit einem ganzen
      Sack voll äußerst praktischer Methoden. Diese Methoden werden immer mit
      einem Punkt abgetrennt hinter dem entsprechenden Objekt
      geschrieben.</fo:block><fo:block space-before.minimum="0.1em" space-before.optimum="0.1em" space-before.maximum="0.1em" space-after.optimum="1em" space-after.minimum="0.8em" space-after.maximum="1.2em">Hier ein paar Beispiele für Methoden der Klasse
      <fo:inline font-family="DejaVuSansMono">String</fo:inline>.<fo:block id="id2547428" text-align="start" wrap-option="wrap" hyphenation-character="\" space-before.minimum="0.8em" space-before.optimum="1em" space-before.maximum="1.2em" space-after.minimum="0.8em" space-after.optimum="1em" space-after.maximum="1.2em" hyphenate="true" white-space-collapse="false" white-space-treatment="preserve" linefeed-treatment="preserve" font-family="DejaVuSansMono" background-color="#FBFEDF" color="black" padding-left="12pt" padding-right="12pt" padding-top="6pt" padding-bottom="6pt" margin-left="0pc">sw@debian:~/sandbox$ <fo:inline font-weight="bold">irb</fo:inline>
irb(main):001:0&gt; <fo:inline font-weight="bold">a = 'Das Haus.'</fo:inline>
=&gt; "Das Haus."
irb(main):002:0&gt; <fo:inline font-weight="bold">a.class</fo:inline>     # .class gibt die Klasse des Objektes aus
=&gt; String
irb(main):003:0&gt; <fo:inline font-weight="bold">a.size</fo:inline>      # Länge des Strings
=&gt; 9
irb(main):004:0&gt; <fo:inline font-weight="bold">a.downcase</fo:inline>  # Umwandlung in Kleinbuchstaben
=&gt; "das haus."
irb(main):005:0&gt; <fo:inline font-weight="bold">a.upcase</fo:inline>    # Umwandlung in Großbuchstaben
=&gt; "DAS HAUS."
irb(main):006:0&gt; <fo:inline font-weight="bold">a.reverse</fo:inline>   # Buchstabenreihenfolge umdrehen
=&gt; ".suaH saD"
irb(main):007:0&gt; <fo:inline font-weight="bold">exit</fo:inline>
</fo:block></fo:block></fo:block><fo:block id="id2547469"><fo:block><fo:block><fo:block margin-left="0pc" font-family="MetaPlusBold,Symbol,ZapfDingbats" keep-together.within-column="always"><fo:block keep-with-next.within-column="always"><fo:block font-family="MetaPlusBold" font-weight="bold" keep-with-next.within-column="always" space-before.minimum="1.8em" space-before.optimum="2.0em" space-before.maximum="2.2em" space-after.minimum="0.1em" space-after.optimum="0.1em" space-after.maximum="0.1em" text-align="left" start-indent="0pc"><fo:marker marker-class-name="section.head.marker">Verketten von Methoden</fo:marker><fo:block color="#000033" font-size="12.6pt">2.7.3. Verketten von Methoden</fo:block></fo:block></fo:block></fo:block></fo:block></fo:block><fo:block space-before.minimum="0.1em" space-before.optimum="0.1em" space-before.maximum="0.1em" space-after.optimum="1em" space-after.minimum="0.8em" space-after.maximum="1.2em">Man kommt nicht direkt drauf, aber wenn man sich an das Arbeiten
      mit Ruby gewöhnt hat, dann ist es auch völlig selbstverständlich (weil
      logisch) verschiedene Methoden zu verketten.<fo:block id="id2547481" text-align="start" wrap-option="wrap" hyphenation-character="\" space-before.minimum="0.8em" space-before.optimum="1em" space-before.maximum="1.2em" space-after.minimum="0.8em" space-after.optimum="1em" space-after.maximum="1.2em" hyphenate="true" white-space-collapse="false" white-space-treatment="preserve" linefeed-treatment="preserve" font-family="DejaVuSansMono" background-color="#FBFEDF" color="black" padding-left="12pt" padding-right="12pt" padding-top="6pt" padding-bottom="6pt" margin-left="0pc">sw@debian:~/sandbox$ <fo:inline font-weight="bold">irb</fo:inline>
irb(main):001:0&gt; <fo:inline font-weight="bold">a = 'Das Haus.'</fo:inline>
=&gt; "Das Haus."
irb(main):002:0&gt; <fo:inline font-weight="bold">a.class</fo:inline>
=&gt; String
irb(main):003:0&gt; <fo:inline font-weight="bold">a.upcase.reverse</fo:inline>  # Großbuchstaben umgedreht
=&gt; ".SUAH SAD"
irb(main):004:0&gt; <fo:inline font-weight="bold">exit</fo:inline>
</fo:block></fo:block></fo:block><fo:block id="id2547507"><fo:block><fo:block><fo:block margin-left="0pc" font-family="MetaPlusBold,Symbol,ZapfDingbats" keep-together.within-column="always"><fo:block keep-with-next.within-column="always"><fo:block font-family="MetaPlusBold" font-weight="bold" keep-with-next.within-column="always" space-before.minimum="1.8em" space-before.optimum="2.0em" space-before.maximum="2.2em" space-after.minimum="0.1em" space-after.optimum="0.1em" space-after.maximum="0.1em" text-align="left" start-indent="0pc"><fo:marker marker-class-name="section.head.marker">Von einem zum anderen (Konvertieren)</fo:marker><fo:block color="#000033" font-size="12.6pt">2.7.4. Von einem zum anderen (Konvertieren)</fo:block></fo:block></fo:block></fo:block></fo:block></fo:block><fo:block space-before.minimum="0.1em" space-before.optimum="0.1em" space-before.maximum="0.1em" space-after.optimum="1em" space-after.minimum="0.8em" space-after.maximum="1.2em">Logischerweise gibt es eine ganze Reihe von praktischen
      Instanz-Methoden um Objekte von einer Klasse in eine andere zu wandeln
      (zu <fo:inline>„cast“</fo:inline>en). Als erstes verwandeln wir mal mit der
      Methode <fo:inline font-family="DejaVuSansMono">.to_s</fo:inline> ein <fo:inline font-family="DejaVuSansMono">Fixnum</fo:inline>
      in einen <fo:inline font-family="DejaVuSansMono">String</fo:inline>.<fo:block id="id2547534" text-align="start" wrap-option="wrap" hyphenation-character="\" space-before.minimum="0.8em" space-before.optimum="1em" space-before.maximum="1.2em" space-after.minimum="0.8em" space-after.optimum="1em" space-after.maximum="1.2em" hyphenate="true" white-space-collapse="false" white-space-treatment="preserve" linefeed-treatment="preserve" font-family="DejaVuSansMono" background-color="#FBFEDF" color="black" padding-left="12pt" padding-right="12pt" padding-top="6pt" padding-bottom="6pt" margin-left="0pc">sw@debian:~/sandbox$ <fo:inline font-weight="bold">irb</fo:inline>
irb(main):001:0&gt; <fo:inline font-weight="bold">a = 10</fo:inline>
=&gt; 10
irb(main):002:0&gt; <fo:inline font-weight="bold">a.class</fo:inline>
=&gt; Fixnum
irb(main):003:0&gt; <fo:inline font-weight="bold">b = a.to_s</fo:inline>
=&gt; "10"
irb(main):004:0&gt; <fo:inline font-weight="bold">exit</fo:inline>
</fo:block></fo:block><fo:block space-before.minimum="0.1em" space-before.optimum="0.1em" space-before.maximum="0.1em" space-after.optimum="1em" space-after.minimum="0.8em" space-after.maximum="1.2em">Nichts anderes macht übrigens <fo:inline font-family="DejaVuSansMono">puts</fo:inline>, wenn man mit
      <fo:inline font-family="DejaVuSansMono">puts</fo:inline> ein <fo:inline font-family="DejaVuSansMono">Fixnum</fo:inline> oder ein
      <fo:inline font-family="DejaVuSansMono">Float</fo:inline> ausgibt (es fügt bei Nicht-Strings einfach
      die Methode <fo:inline font-family="DejaVuSansMono">.to_s</fo:inline> hinzu und gibt das Ergebnis
      aus).</fo:block><fo:block space-before.minimum="0.1em" space-before.optimum="0.1em" space-before.maximum="0.1em" space-after.optimum="1em" space-after.minimum="0.8em" space-after.maximum="1.2em">Jetzt wandeln wir mal mit der Methode
      <fo:inline font-family="DejaVuSansMono">.to_i</fo:inline> ein <fo:inline font-family="DejaVuSansMono">Float</fo:inline> in ein
      <fo:inline font-family="DejaVuSansMono">Fixnum</fo:inline> um.<fo:block id="id2547597" text-align="start" wrap-option="wrap" hyphenation-character="\" space-before.minimum="0.8em" space-before.optimum="1em" space-before.maximum="1.2em" space-after.minimum="0.8em" space-after.optimum="1em" space-after.maximum="1.2em" hyphenate="true" white-space-collapse="false" white-space-treatment="preserve" linefeed-treatment="preserve" font-family="DejaVuSansMono" background-color="#FBFEDF" color="black" padding-left="12pt" padding-right="12pt" padding-top="6pt" padding-bottom="6pt" margin-left="0pc">sw@debian:~/sandbox$ <fo:inline font-weight="bold">irb</fo:inline>
irb(main):001:0&gt; <fo:inline font-weight="bold">c = 10.0</fo:inline>
=&gt; 10.0
irb(main):002:0&gt; <fo:inline font-weight="bold">c.class</fo:inline>
=&gt; Float
irb(main):003:0&gt; <fo:inline font-weight="bold">d = c.to_i</fo:inline>
=&gt; 10
irb(main):004:0&gt; <fo:inline font-weight="bold">d.class</fo:inline>
=&gt; Fixnum
irb(main):005:0&gt; <fo:inline font-weight="bold">exit</fo:inline>
</fo:block></fo:block></fo:block><fo:block id="id2547626"><fo:block><fo:block><fo:block margin-left="0pc" font-family="MetaPlusBold,Symbol,ZapfDingbats" keep-together.within-column="always"><fo:block keep-with-next.within-column="always"><fo:block font-family="MetaPlusBold" font-weight="bold" keep-with-next.within-column="always" space-before.minimum="1.8em" space-before.optimum="2.0em" space-before.maximum="2.2em" space-after.minimum="0.1em" space-after.optimum="0.1em" space-after.maximum="0.1em" text-align="left" start-indent="0pc"><fo:marker marker-class-name="section.head.marker">Methode to_s bei eigenen Klassen</fo:marker><fo:block color="#000033" font-size="12.6pt">2.7.5. Methode to_s bei eigenen Klassen</fo:block></fo:block></fo:block></fo:block></fo:block></fo:block><fo:block space-before.minimum="0.1em" space-before.optimum="0.1em" space-before.maximum="0.1em" space-after.optimum="1em" space-after.minimum="0.8em" space-after.maximum="1.2em">Man sollte – und wenn es nur für das einfachere Debugging ist –
      bei selbstdefinierten Klassen immer eine Methode
      <fo:inline font-family="DejaVuSansMono">to_s</fo:inline> einbauen. Dann kann man ein entsprechendes
      Objekt einfach mit <fo:inline font-family="DejaVuSansMono">puts</fo:inline> ausgeben (<fo:inline font-family="DejaVuSansMono">puts</fo:inline> gibt
      ein Objekt automatisch unter Verwendung der Methode
      <fo:inline font-family="DejaVuSansMono">to_s</fo:inline> aus).</fo:block><fo:block space-before.minimum="0.1em" space-before.optimum="0.1em" space-before.maximum="0.1em" space-after.optimum="1em" space-after.minimum="0.8em" space-after.maximum="1.2em">Ein Beispiel:<fo:block id="id2547658" text-align="start" wrap-option="wrap" hyphenation-character="\" space-before.minimum="0.8em" space-before.optimum="1em" space-before.maximum="1.2em" space-after.minimum="0.8em" space-after.optimum="1em" space-after.maximum="1.2em" hyphenate="true" white-space-collapse="false" white-space-treatment="preserve" linefeed-treatment="preserve" font-family="DejaVuSansMono" background-color="#FBFEDF" color="black" padding-left="12pt" padding-right="12pt" padding-top="6pt" padding-bottom="6pt" margin-left="0pc">sw@debian:~/sandbox$ <fo:inline font-weight="bold">irb</fo:inline>
irb(main):001:0&gt; <fo:inline font-weight="bold">class Tier</fo:inline>
irb(main):002:1&gt; <fo:inline font-weight="bold">  def initialize(de_name,en_name)</fo:inline>
irb(main):003:2&gt; <fo:inline font-weight="bold">    @de_name = de_name</fo:inline>
irb(main):004:2&gt; <fo:inline font-weight="bold">    @en_name = en_name</fo:inline>
irb(main):005:2&gt; <fo:inline font-weight="bold">  end</fo:inline>
irb(main):006:1&gt; <fo:inline font-weight="bold">  def to_s</fo:inline>
irb(main):007:2&gt; <fo:inline font-weight="bold">    @de_name + ' (' + @en_name + ')'</fo:inline>
irb(main):008:2&gt; <fo:inline font-weight="bold">  end</fo:inline>
irb(main):009:1&gt; <fo:inline font-weight="bold">end</fo:inline>
=&gt; nil
irb(main):010:0&gt; <fo:inline font-weight="bold">lumpi = Tier.new('Hund', 'Dog')</fo:inline>
=&gt; #&lt;Tier:0x873b5c8 @de_name="Hund", @en_name="Dog"&gt;
irb(main):011:0&gt; <fo:inline font-weight="bold">hansi = Tier.new('Wellensittich', 'Budgerigar')</fo:inline>           
=&gt; #&lt;Tier:0x86b60f8 @de_name="Wellensittich", @en_name="Budgerigar"&gt;
irb(main):012:0&gt; <fo:inline font-weight="bold">puts lumpi</fo:inline>
Hund(Dog)
=&gt; nil
irb(main):013:0&gt; <fo:inline font-weight="bold">puts hansi</fo:inline>
Wellensittich(Budgerigar)
=&gt; nil
irb(main):014:0&gt; <fo:inline font-weight="bold">exit</fo:inline>
</fo:block></fo:block></fo:block><fo:block id="id2547727"><fo:block><fo:block><fo:block margin-left="0pc" font-family="MetaPlusBold,Symbol,ZapfDingbats" keep-together.within-column="always"><fo:block keep-with-next.within-column="always"><fo:block font-family="MetaPlusBold" font-weight="bold" keep-with-next.within-column="always" space-before.minimum="1.8em" space-before.optimum="2.0em" space-before.maximum="2.2em" space-after.minimum="0.1em" space-after.optimum="0.1em" space-after.maximum="0.1em" text-align="left" start-indent="0pc"><fo:marker marker-class-name="section.head.marker">Ist <fo:inline>„+“</fo:inline> eine Methode?</fo:marker><fo:block color="#000033" font-size="12.6pt">2.7.6. Ist <fo:inline>„+“</fo:inline> eine Methode?</fo:block></fo:block></fo:block></fo:block></fo:block></fo:block><fo:block space-before.minimum="0.1em" space-before.optimum="0.1em" space-before.maximum="0.1em" space-after.optimum="1em" space-after.minimum="0.8em" space-after.maximum="1.2em">Wieso steht bei der Liste der Methoden beim
      <fo:inline font-family="DejaVuSansMono">String</fo:inline> auch das Pluszeichen? Schauen wir mal mit
      ri nach:<fo:block id="id2547748" text-align="start" wrap-option="wrap" hyphenation-character="\" space-before.minimum="0.8em" space-before.optimum="1em" space-before.maximum="1.2em" space-after.minimum="0.8em" space-after.optimum="1em" space-after.maximum="1.2em" hyphenate="true" white-space-collapse="false" white-space-treatment="preserve" linefeed-treatment="preserve" font-family="DejaVuSansMono" background-color="#FBFEDF" color="black" padding-left="12pt" padding-right="12pt" padding-top="6pt" padding-bottom="6pt" margin-left="0pc">sw@debian:~/sandbox$ <fo:inline font-weight="bold">ri String.+</fo:inline>
--------------------------------------------------------------- String#+
     str + other_str   =&gt; new_str

     From Ruby 1.9.1
------------------------------------------------------------------------
     Concatenation---Returns a new +String+ containing _other_str_
     concatenated to _str_.

        "Hello from " + self.to_s   #=&gt; "Hello from main"

sw@debian:~/sandbox$</fo:block></fo:block><fo:block space-before.minimum="0.1em" space-before.optimum="0.1em" space-before.maximum="0.1em" space-after.optimum="1em" space-after.minimum="0.8em" space-after.maximum="1.2em">hmmm… Mal schauen was da bei <fo:inline font-family="DejaVuSansMono">Fixnum</fo:inline>
      steht:<fo:block id="id2547768" text-align="start" wrap-option="wrap" hyphenation-character="\" space-before.minimum="0.8em" space-before.optimum="1em" space-before.maximum="1.2em" space-after.minimum="0.8em" space-after.optimum="1em" space-after.maximum="1.2em" hyphenate="true" white-space-collapse="false" white-space-treatment="preserve" linefeed-treatment="preserve" font-family="DejaVuSansMono" background-color="#FBFEDF" color="black" padding-left="12pt" padding-right="12pt" padding-top="6pt" padding-bottom="6pt" margin-left="0pc">sw@debian:~/sandbox$ <fo:inline font-weight="bold">ri Fixnum.+</fo:inline>
--------------------------------------------------------------- Fixnum#+
     fix + numeric   =&gt;  numeric_result

     From Ruby 1.9.1
------------------------------------------------------------------------
     Performs addition: the class of the resulting object depends on the
     class of +numeric+ and on the magnitude of the result.

sw@debian:~/sandbox$</fo:block></fo:block><fo:block space-before.minimum="0.1em" space-before.optimum="0.1em" space-before.maximum="0.1em" space-after.optimum="1em" space-after.minimum="0.8em" space-after.maximum="1.2em">Spielen wir damit mal im irb. Wir müssten ja dann das
      <fo:inline font-family="DejaVuSansMono">+</fo:inline> genauso wie jede andere Methode mit einem
      Punkt an die Class hängen können und die zweite Zahl in einer Klammer
      als Parameter anfügen.<fo:block id="id2547791" text-align="start" wrap-option="wrap" hyphenation-character="\" space-before.minimum="0.8em" space-before.optimum="1em" space-before.maximum="1.2em" space-after.minimum="0.8em" space-after.optimum="1em" space-after.maximum="1.2em" hyphenate="true" white-space-collapse="false" white-space-treatment="preserve" linefeed-treatment="preserve" font-family="DejaVuSansMono" background-color="#FBFEDF" color="black" padding-left="12pt" padding-right="12pt" padding-top="6pt" padding-bottom="6pt" margin-left="0pc">sw@debian:~/sandbox$ <fo:inline font-weight="bold">irb</fo:inline>
irb(main):001:0&gt; <fo:inline font-weight="bold">10 + 10</fo:inline>
=&gt; 20
irb(main):002:0&gt; <fo:inline font-weight="bold">10+10</fo:inline>
=&gt; 20
irb(main):003:0&gt; <fo:inline font-weight="bold">10.+10</fo:inline>
=&gt; 20
irb(main):004:0&gt; <fo:inline font-weight="bold">10.+(10)</fo:inline>
=&gt; 20
irb(main):005:0&gt; <fo:inline font-weight="bold">exit</fo:inline>
</fo:block></fo:block><fo:block space-before.minimum="0.1em" space-before.optimum="0.1em" space-before.maximum="0.1em" space-after.optimum="1em" space-after.minimum="0.8em" space-after.maximum="1.2em">Aha! Das Pluszeichen ist tatsächlich eine Methode, und diese
      Methode nimmt den nächsten Wert als Parameter. Eigentlich müssten wir
      diesen Wert in einer Klammer setzen, aber Ruby erspart uns das mit
      durchdachter Syntax.</fo:block><fo:block id="id2547827"><fo:block><fo:block><fo:block margin-left="0pc" font-family="MetaPlusBold,Symbol,ZapfDingbats" keep-together.within-column="always"><fo:block keep-with-next.within-column="always"><fo:block font-family="MetaPlusBold" font-weight="bold" keep-with-next.within-column="always" space-before.minimum="1.8em" space-before.optimum="2.0em" space-before.maximum="2.2em" space-after.minimum="0.1em" space-after.optimum="0.1em" space-after.maximum="0.1em" text-align="left" start-indent="0pc"><fo:block color="#000033" font-size="11.7pt">2.7.6.1. Kann ich die Methode + überschreiben?</fo:block></fo:block></fo:block></fo:block></fo:block></fo:block><fo:block space-before.minimum="0.1em" space-before.optimum="0.1em" space-before.maximum="0.1em" space-after.optimum="1em" space-after.minimum="0.8em" space-after.maximum="1.2em">Ja, man kann alle Methoden überschreiben. Logischerweise macht
        das bei Methoden wie <fo:inline font-family="DejaVuSansMono">+</fo:inline> wenig Sinn, außer man
        will damit seine Programmierkollegen in den Wahnsinn treiben. Damit
        Sie mir glauben führe ich jetzt im irb mal eine kleine Demo
        aus.</fo:block><fo:block space-before.minimum="0.1em" space-before.optimum="0.1em" space-before.maximum="0.1em" space-after.optimum="1em" space-after.minimum="0.8em" space-after.maximum="1.2em">Das Ziel ist es die Methode <fo:inline font-family="DejaVuSansMono">+</fo:inline> für
        <fo:inline font-family="DejaVuSansMono">Fixnum</fo:inline> zu überschreiben. Als Ergebnis jeder
        Addition soll die Zahl 42 rauskommen.<fo:block id="id2547857" text-align="start" wrap-option="wrap" hyphenation-character="\" space-before.minimum="0.8em" space-before.optimum="1em" space-before.maximum="1.2em" space-after.minimum="0.8em" space-after.optimum="1em" space-after.maximum="1.2em" hyphenate="true" white-space-collapse="false" white-space-treatment="preserve" linefeed-treatment="preserve" font-family="DejaVuSansMono" background-color="#FBFEDF" color="black" padding-left="12pt" padding-right="12pt" padding-top="6pt" padding-bottom="6pt" margin-left="0pc">sw@debian:~/sandbox$ <fo:inline font-weight="bold">irb</fo:inline>
irb(main):001:0&gt; <fo:inline font-weight="bold">10 + 10</fo:inline>
=&gt; 20
irb(main):002:0&gt; <fo:inline font-weight="bold">10 + 5555</fo:inline>
=&gt; 5565
irb(main):003:0&gt; <fo:inline font-weight="bold">class Fixnum</fo:inline> 
irb(main):004:1&gt; <fo:inline font-weight="bold">  def +(name, *args, &amp;blk)</fo:inline>
irb(main):005:2&gt; <fo:inline font-weight="bold">    42</fo:inline>
irb(main):006:2&gt; <fo:inline font-weight="bold">  end</fo:inline>
irb(main):007:1&gt; <fo:inline font-weight="bold">end</fo:inline>
=&gt; nil
irb(main):008:0&gt; <fo:inline font-weight="bold">10 + 10</fo:inline>
=&gt; 42
irb(main):042:0&gt; <fo:inline font-weight="bold">10 + 5555</fo:inline>
=&gt; 42
irb(main):042:0&gt; <fo:inline font-weight="bold">exit</fo:inline>
</fo:block></fo:block><fo:block space-before.minimum="0.1em" space-before.optimum="0.1em" space-before.maximum="0.1em" space-after.optimum="1em" space-after.minimum="0.8em" space-after.maximum="1.2em">In den Zeilen 1 und 2 führen wir die normale Addition durch. In
        den Zeilen 3 bis 7 definieren wir die Methode
        <fo:inline font-family="DejaVuSansMono">+</fo:inline> für die Class <fo:inline font-family="DejaVuSansMono">Fixnum</fo:inline>
        neu, und danach führen wir noch einmal die Berechnung durch. Dann
        allerdings mit anderen Ergebnissen.</fo:block></fo:block><fo:block id="id2547921"><fo:block><fo:block><fo:block margin-left="0pc" font-family="MetaPlusBold,Symbol,ZapfDingbats" keep-together.within-column="always"><fo:block keep-with-next.within-column="always"><fo:block font-family="MetaPlusBold" font-weight="bold" keep-with-next.within-column="always" space-before.minimum="1.8em" space-before.optimum="2.0em" space-before.maximum="2.2em" space-after.minimum="0.1em" space-after.optimum="0.1em" space-after.maximum="0.1em" text-align="left" start-indent="0pc"><fo:block color="#000033" font-size="11.7pt">2.7.6.2. Liste aller Methoden für eine bestimmte Class</fo:block></fo:block></fo:block></fo:block></fo:block></fo:block><fo:block space-before.minimum="0.1em" space-before.optimum="0.1em" space-before.maximum="0.1em" space-after.optimum="1em" space-after.minimum="0.8em" space-after.maximum="1.2em">Nun hat man nicht immer alle Methoden-Namen im Kopf, weiß aber
        dass es für das spezielle Problem eine perfekte Methode gibt (passiert
        mir ständig).</fo:block><fo:block id="id2547934"><fo:block><fo:block><fo:block margin-left="0pc" font-family="MetaPlusBold,Symbol,ZapfDingbats" keep-together.within-column="always"><fo:block keep-with-next.within-column="always"><fo:block font-family="MetaPlusBold" font-weight="bold" keep-with-next.within-column="always" space-before.minimum="1.8em" space-before.optimum="2.0em" space-before.maximum="2.2em" space-after.minimum="0.1em" space-after.optimum="0.1em" space-after.maximum="0.1em" text-align="left" start-indent="0pc"><fo:block color="#000033" font-size="10.8pt">2.7.6.2.1. Im irb</fo:block></fo:block></fo:block></fo:block></fo:block></fo:block><fo:block space-before.minimum="0.1em" space-before.optimum="0.1em" space-before.maximum="0.1em" space-after.optimum="1em" space-after.minimum="0.8em" space-after.maximum="1.2em">Mit der Methode <fo:inline font-family="DejaVuSansMono">methods</fo:inline> kann man die
          zur Verfügung stehenden Methoden anzeigen. Allerdings weiß man dann
          nicht unbedingt was diese genau machen.<fo:block id="id2547949" text-align="start" wrap-option="wrap" hyphenation-character="\" space-before.minimum="0.8em" space-before.optimum="1em" space-before.maximum="1.2em" space-after.minimum="0.8em" space-after.optimum="1em" space-after.maximum="1.2em" hyphenate="true" white-space-collapse="false" white-space-treatment="preserve" linefeed-treatment="preserve" font-family="DejaVuSansMono" background-color="#FBFEDF" color="black" padding-left="12pt" padding-right="12pt" padding-top="6pt" padding-bottom="6pt" margin-left="0pc">sw@debian:~/sandbox$ <fo:inline font-weight="bold">irb</fo:inline>
irb(main):001:0&gt; <fo:inline font-weight="bold">a = 'Das blaue Haus.'</fo:inline>
=&gt; "Das blaue Haus."
irb(main):002:0&gt; <fo:inline font-weight="bold">a.methods</fo:inline>
=&gt; [:&lt;=&gt;, :==, :===, :eql?, :hash, :casecmp, :+, :*, :%, :[], :[]=, :insert, :length, :size, :bytesize, :empty?, :=~, :match, :succ, :succ!, :next, :next!, :upto, :index, :rindex, :replace, :clear, :chr, :getbyte, :setbyte, :to_i, :to_f, :to_s, :to_str, :inspect, :dump, :upcase, :downcase, :capitalize, :swapcase, :upcase!, :downcase!, :capitalize!, :swapcase!, :hex, :oct, :split, :lines, :bytes, :chars, :codepoints, :reverse, :reverse!, :concat, :&lt;&lt;, :crypt, :intern, :to_sym, :ord, :include?, :start_with?, :end_with?, :scan, :ljust, :rjust, :center, :sub, :gsub, :chop, :chomp, :strip, :lstrip, :rstrip, :sub!, :gsub!, :chop!, :chomp!, :strip!, :lstrip!, :rstrip!, :tr, :tr_s, :delete, :squeeze, :count, :tr!, :tr_s!, :delete!, :squeeze!, :each_line, :each_byte, :each_char, :each_codepoint, :sum, :slice, :slice!, :partition, :rpartition, :encoding, :force_encoding, :valid_encoding?, :ascii_only?, :unpack, :encode, :encode!, :to_r, :to_c, :&gt;, :&gt;=, :&lt;, :&lt;=, :between?, :nil?, :!~, :class, :clone, :dup, :taint, :tainted?, :untaint, :untrust, :untrusted?, :trust, :freeze, :frozen?, :methods, :singleton_methods, :protected_methods, :private_methods, :public_methods, :instance_variables, :instance_variable_get, :instance_variable_set, :instance_variable_defined?, :instance_of?, :kind_of?, :is_a?, :tap, :send, :public_send, :respond_to?, :extend, :display, :method, :public_method, :define_singleton_method, :__id__, :object_id, :to_enum, :enum_for, :gem, :equal?, :!, :!=, :instance_eval, :instance_exec, :__send__]
irb(main):003:0&gt; <fo:inline font-weight="bold">exit</fo:inline>
</fo:block></fo:block></fo:block></fo:block></fo:block></fo:block><fo:block id="ruby-if-condition"><fo:block><fo:block><fo:block margin-left="0pc" font-family="MetaPlusBold,Symbol,ZapfDingbats" keep-together.within-column="always"><fo:block keep-with-next.within-column="always"><fo:block font-family="MetaPlusBold" font-weight="bold" keep-with-next.within-column="always" space-before.minimum="1.8em" space-before.optimum="2.0em" space-before.maximum="2.2em" space-after.minimum="0.1em" space-after.optimum="0.1em" space-after.maximum="0.1em" text-align="left" start-indent="0pc"><fo:marker marker-class-name="section.head.marker">if-Bedingung (if-Condition)</fo:marker><fo:block color="#000033" font-size="14.4pt">2.8. if-Bedingung (if-Condition)</fo:block></fo:block></fo:block></fo:block></fo:block></fo:block><fo:block space-before.minimum="0.1em" space-before.optimum="0.1em" space-before.maximum="0.1em" space-after.optimum="1em" space-after.minimum="0.8em" space-after.maximum="1.2em">Eine abstrakte <fo:inline font-family="DejaVuSansMono">if</fo:inline>-Bedingung sieht so
    aus:<fo:block id="id2548016" text-align="start" wrap-option="wrap" hyphenation-character="\" space-before.minimum="0.8em" space-before.optimum="1em" space-before.maximum="1.2em" space-after.minimum="0.8em" space-after.optimum="1em" space-after.maximum="1.2em" hyphenate="true" white-space-collapse="false" white-space-treatment="preserve" linefeed-treatment="preserve" font-family="DejaVuSansMono" background-color="#FBFEDF" color="black" padding-left="12pt" padding-right="12pt" padding-top="6pt" padding-bottom="6pt" margin-left="0pc">if ausdruck
  programm
end</fo:block></fo:block><fo:block space-before.minimum="0.1em" space-before.optimum="0.1em" space-before.maximum="0.1em" space-after.optimum="1em" space-after.minimum="0.8em" space-after.maximum="1.2em">Das Programm zwischen dem Ausdruck (Expression) und <fo:inline font-family="DejaVuSansMono">end</fo:inline>
    wird immer dann ausgeführt, wenn das Ergebnis des Ausdrucks nicht
    <fo:inline font-family="DejaVuSansMono">false</fo:inline> und nicht <fo:inline font-family="DejaVuSansMono">nil</fo:inline> ist.</fo:block><fo:block space-before.minimum="0.1em" space-before.optimum="0.1em" space-before.maximum="0.1em" space-after.optimum="1em" space-after.minimum="0.8em" space-after.maximum="1.2em">Das Konstrukt für eine einfache <fo:inline font-family="DejaVuSansMono">if</fo:inline>-Verzweigung in
    einem Ruby-Programm sieht wie folgendes Beispielprogramm
    aus:<fo:block id="id2548045" text-align="start" wrap-option="wrap" hyphenation-character="\" space-before.minimum="0.8em" space-before.optimum="1em" space-before.maximum="1.2em" space-after.minimum="0.8em" space-after.optimum="1em" space-after.maximum="1.2em" hyphenate="true" white-space-collapse="false" white-space-treatment="preserve" linefeed-treatment="preserve" font-family="DejaVuSansMono" background-color="#FBFEDF" color="black" padding-left="12pt" padding-right="12pt" padding-top="6pt" padding-bottom="6pt" margin-left="0pc">a = 10

<fo:inline font-weight="bold">if a == 10 then</fo:inline>    # a == 10 ist die Expression
  puts 'a ist 10'  # das Programm
<fo:inline font-weight="bold">end</fo:inline>
</fo:block></fo:block><fo:block space-before.minimum="0.1em" space-before.optimum="0.1em" space-before.maximum="0.1em" space-after.optimum="1em" space-after.minimum="0.8em" space-after.maximum="1.2em">Eine Expression kann man sehr gut im irb ausprobieren:<fo:block id="id2548065" text-align="start" wrap-option="wrap" hyphenation-character="\" space-before.minimum="0.8em" space-before.optimum="1em" space-before.maximum="1.2em" space-after.minimum="0.8em" space-after.optimum="1em" space-after.maximum="1.2em" hyphenate="true" white-space-collapse="false" white-space-treatment="preserve" linefeed-treatment="preserve" font-family="DejaVuSansMono" background-color="#FBFEDF" color="black" padding-left="12pt" padding-right="12pt" padding-top="6pt" padding-bottom="6pt" margin-left="0pc">sw@debian:~/sandbox$ <fo:inline font-weight="bold">irb</fo:inline>
irb(main):001:0&gt; <fo:inline font-weight="bold">a = 10</fo:inline>
=&gt; 10
irb(main):002:0&gt; <fo:inline font-weight="bold">a == 10</fo:inline>
=&gt; true
irb(main):003:0&gt; <fo:inline font-weight="bold">exit</fo:inline>
</fo:block></fo:block><fo:block id="id2548084"><fo:block><fo:block><fo:block margin-left="0pc" font-family="MetaPlusBold,Symbol,ZapfDingbats" keep-together.within-column="always"><fo:block keep-with-next.within-column="always"><fo:block font-family="MetaPlusBold" font-weight="bold" keep-with-next.within-column="always" space-before.minimum="1.8em" space-before.optimum="2.0em" space-before.maximum="2.2em" space-after.minimum="0.1em" space-after.optimum="0.1em" space-after.maximum="0.1em" text-align="left" start-indent="0pc"><fo:marker marker-class-name="section.head.marker">Kurzform</fo:marker><fo:block color="#000033" font-size="12.6pt">2.8.1. Kurzform</fo:block></fo:block></fo:block></fo:block></fo:block></fo:block><fo:block space-before.minimum="0.1em" space-before.optimum="0.1em" space-before.maximum="0.1em" space-after.optimum="1em" space-after.minimum="0.8em" space-after.maximum="1.2em">Eine häufig anzutreffende Kurzform einer
      <fo:inline font-family="DejaVuSansMono">if</fo:inline>-Condition ist im folgenden Code zu
      finden:<fo:block id="id2548098" text-align="start" wrap-option="wrap" hyphenation-character="\" space-before.minimum="0.8em" space-before.optimum="1em" space-before.maximum="1.2em" space-after.minimum="0.8em" space-after.optimum="1em" space-after.maximum="1.2em" hyphenate="true" white-space-collapse="false" white-space-treatment="preserve" linefeed-treatment="preserve" font-family="DejaVuSansMono" background-color="#FBFEDF" color="black" padding-left="12pt" padding-right="12pt" padding-top="6pt" padding-bottom="6pt" margin-left="0pc">a = 10

# Langversion
#
if a == 10 then
  puts 'a ist 10'           # Die Programmzeile ist von if und end eingeschlossen.
end

# Kurzversion
#
<fo:inline font-weight="bold">puts 'a ist 10' if a == 10</fo:inline>  # das if folgt der Programmzeile</fo:block></fo:block></fo:block><fo:block id="id2548112"><fo:block><fo:block><fo:block margin-left="0pc" font-family="MetaPlusBold,Symbol,ZapfDingbats" keep-together.within-column="always"><fo:block keep-with-next.within-column="always"><fo:block font-family="MetaPlusBold" font-weight="bold" keep-with-next.within-column="always" space-before.minimum="1.8em" space-before.optimum="2.0em" space-before.maximum="2.2em" space-after.minimum="0.1em" space-after.optimum="0.1em" space-after.maximum="0.1em" text-align="left" start-indent="0pc"><fo:marker marker-class-name="section.head.marker">else</fo:marker><fo:block color="#000033" font-size="12.6pt">2.8.2. else</fo:block></fo:block></fo:block></fo:block></fo:block></fo:block><fo:block space-before.minimum="0.1em" space-before.optimum="0.1em" space-before.maximum="0.1em" space-after.optimum="1em" space-after.minimum="0.8em" space-after.maximum="1.2em">Man kann es sich schon denken, aber der Vollständigkeit halber
      auch hierzu noch ein kleines Beispiel:<fo:block id="id2548122" text-align="start" wrap-option="wrap" hyphenation-character="\" space-before.minimum="0.8em" space-before.optimum="1em" space-before.maximum="1.2em" space-after.minimum="0.8em" space-after.optimum="1em" space-after.maximum="1.2em" hyphenate="true" white-space-collapse="false" white-space-treatment="preserve" linefeed-treatment="preserve" font-family="DejaVuSansMono" background-color="#FBFEDF" color="black" padding-left="12pt" padding-right="12pt" padding-top="6pt" padding-bottom="6pt" margin-left="0pc">a = 10

if a == 10 then
  puts 'a ist 10'
else
  puts 'a ist nicht 10'
end
</fo:block></fo:block></fo:block></fo:block><fo:block id="ruby-schleifen"><fo:block><fo:block><fo:block margin-left="0pc" font-family="MetaPlusBold,Symbol,ZapfDingbats" keep-together.within-column="always"><fo:block keep-with-next.within-column="always"><fo:block font-family="MetaPlusBold" font-weight="bold" keep-with-next.within-column="always" space-before.minimum="1.8em" space-before.optimum="2.0em" space-before.maximum="2.2em" space-after.minimum="0.1em" space-after.optimum="0.1em" space-after.maximum="0.1em" text-align="left" start-indent="0pc"><fo:marker marker-class-name="section.head.marker">Schleifen</fo:marker><fo:block color="#000033" font-size="14.4pt">2.9. Schleifen</fo:block></fo:block></fo:block></fo:block></fo:block></fo:block><fo:block space-before.minimum="0.1em" space-before.optimum="0.1em" space-before.maximum="0.1em" space-after.optimum="1em" space-after.minimum="0.8em" space-after.maximum="1.2em">Es gibt verschiedenen Arten Schleifen in Ruby zu realisieren. Dabei
    kommt im Rails-Umfeld vor allen Dingen die Iterator-Variante häufig zum
    Einsatz.</fo:block><fo:block id="id2548146"><fo:block><fo:block><fo:block margin-left="0pc" font-family="MetaPlusBold,Symbol,ZapfDingbats" keep-together.within-column="always"><fo:block keep-with-next.within-column="always"><fo:block font-family="MetaPlusBold" font-weight="bold" keep-with-next.within-column="always" space-before.minimum="1.8em" space-before.optimum="2.0em" space-before.maximum="2.2em" space-after.minimum="0.1em" space-after.optimum="0.1em" space-after.maximum="0.1em" text-align="left" start-indent="0pc"><fo:marker marker-class-name="section.head.marker">while und until</fo:marker><fo:block color="#000033" font-size="12.6pt">2.9.1. while und until</fo:block></fo:block></fo:block></fo:block></fo:block></fo:block><fo:block space-before.minimum="0.1em" space-before.optimum="0.1em" space-before.maximum="0.1em" space-after.optimum="1em" space-after.minimum="0.8em" space-after.maximum="1.2em">Eine While-Schleife sieht abstrakt wie folgt aus:<fo:block id="id2548155" text-align="start" wrap-option="wrap" hyphenation-character="\" space-before.minimum="0.8em" space-before.optimum="1em" space-before.maximum="1.2em" space-after.minimum="0.8em" space-after.optimum="1em" space-after.maximum="1.2em" hyphenate="true" white-space-collapse="false" white-space-treatment="preserve" linefeed-treatment="preserve" font-family="DejaVuSansMono" background-color="#FBFEDF" color="black" padding-left="12pt" padding-right="12pt" padding-top="6pt" padding-bottom="6pt" margin-left="0pc">while ausdruck do
  programm
end</fo:block></fo:block><fo:block space-before.minimum="0.1em" space-before.optimum="0.1em" space-before.maximum="0.1em" space-after.optimum="1em" space-after.minimum="0.8em" space-after.maximum="1.2em">Und praktisch wie in folgendem irb-Beispiel:<fo:block id="id2548162" text-align="start" wrap-option="wrap" hyphenation-character="\" space-before.minimum="0.8em" space-before.optimum="1em" space-before.maximum="1.2em" space-after.minimum="0.8em" space-after.optimum="1em" space-after.maximum="1.2em" hyphenate="true" white-space-collapse="false" white-space-treatment="preserve" linefeed-treatment="preserve" font-family="DejaVuSansMono" background-color="#FBFEDF" color="black" padding-left="12pt" padding-right="12pt" padding-top="6pt" padding-bottom="6pt" margin-left="0pc">irb(main):001:0&gt; <fo:inline font-weight="bold">i = 0</fo:inline>             # i wird auf 0 gesetzt
=&gt; 0
irb(main):002:0&gt; <fo:inline font-weight="bold">while i &lt; 3 do</fo:inline>   # Schleife
irb(main):003:1&gt; <fo:inline font-weight="bold">  puts i</fo:inline>          # i wird ausgegeben
irb(main):004:1&gt; <fo:inline font-weight="bold">  i = i + 1</fo:inline>       # i wird um 1 erhöht
irb(main):005:1&gt; <fo:inline font-weight="bold">end</fo:inline>               # Ende der Schleife
0
1
2
=&gt; nil
irb(main):006:0&gt; <fo:inline font-weight="bold">exit</fo:inline>
</fo:block></fo:block><fo:block space-before.minimum="0.1em" space-before.optimum="0.1em" space-before.maximum="0.1em" space-after.optimum="1em" space-after.minimum="0.8em" space-after.maximum="1.2em">Until-Schleifen werden ähnlich aufgebaut:<fo:block id="id2548195" text-align="start" wrap-option="wrap" hyphenation-character="\" space-before.minimum="0.8em" space-before.optimum="1em" space-before.maximum="1.2em" space-after.minimum="0.8em" space-after.optimum="1em" space-after.maximum="1.2em" hyphenate="true" white-space-collapse="false" white-space-treatment="preserve" linefeed-treatment="preserve" font-family="DejaVuSansMono" background-color="#FBFEDF" color="black" padding-left="12pt" padding-right="12pt" padding-top="6pt" padding-bottom="6pt" margin-left="0pc">until ausdruck
  programm
end</fo:block></fo:block><fo:block space-before.minimum="0.1em" space-before.optimum="0.1em" space-before.maximum="0.1em" space-after.optimum="1em" space-after.minimum="0.8em" space-after.maximum="1.2em">Auch hier das irb-Beispiel:<fo:block id="id2548202" text-align="start" wrap-option="wrap" hyphenation-character="\" space-before.minimum="0.8em" space-before.optimum="1em" space-before.maximum="1.2em" space-after.minimum="0.8em" space-after.optimum="1em" space-after.maximum="1.2em" hyphenate="true" white-space-collapse="false" white-space-treatment="preserve" linefeed-treatment="preserve" font-family="DejaVuSansMono" background-color="#FBFEDF" color="black" padding-left="12pt" padding-right="12pt" padding-top="6pt" padding-bottom="6pt" margin-left="0pc">sw@debian:~/sandbox$ <fo:inline font-weight="bold">irb</fo:inline>
irb(main):001:0&gt; <fo:inline font-weight="bold">i = 5</fo:inline>
=&gt; 5
irb(main):002:0&gt; <fo:inline font-weight="bold">until i == 0</fo:inline>
irb(main):003:1&gt; <fo:inline font-weight="bold">i = i - 1</fo:inline>
irb(main):004:1&gt; <fo:inline font-weight="bold">puts i</fo:inline>
irb(main):005:1&gt; <fo:inline font-weight="bold">end</fo:inline>
4
3
2
1
0
=&gt; nil
irb(main):006:0&gt; <fo:inline font-weight="bold">exit</fo:inline>
</fo:block></fo:block></fo:block><fo:block id="id2548234"><fo:block><fo:block><fo:block margin-left="0pc" font-family="MetaPlusBold,Symbol,ZapfDingbats" keep-together.within-column="always"><fo:block keep-with-next.within-column="always"><fo:block font-family="MetaPlusBold" font-weight="bold" keep-with-next.within-column="always" space-before.minimum="1.8em" space-before.optimum="2.0em" space-before.maximum="2.2em" space-after.minimum="0.1em" space-after.optimum="0.1em" space-after.maximum="0.1em" text-align="left" start-indent="0pc"><fo:marker marker-class-name="section.head.marker">Blöcke (Blocks) und Iteratoren (Iterators)</fo:marker><fo:block color="#000033" font-size="12.6pt">2.9.2. Blöcke (Blocks) und Iteratoren (Iterators)</fo:block></fo:block></fo:block></fo:block></fo:block></fo:block><fo:block space-before.minimum="0.1em" space-before.optimum="0.1em" space-before.maximum="0.1em" space-after.optimum="1em" space-after.minimum="0.8em" space-after.maximum="1.2em"><fo:inline>„Block“</fo:inline> und <fo:inline>„Iterator“</fo:inline> gehören zu den
      Lieblingswörter vieler Ruby-Programmierer. Jetzt zeige ich Ihnen mal
      warum.</fo:block><fo:block space-before.minimum="0.1em" space-before.optimum="0.1em" space-before.maximum="0.1em" space-after.optimum="1em" space-after.minimum="0.8em" space-after.maximum="1.2em">Bei der Schleife<fo:block id="id2548255" text-align="start" wrap-option="wrap" hyphenation-character="\" space-before.minimum="0.8em" space-before.optimum="1em" space-before.maximum="1.2em" space-after.minimum="0.8em" space-after.optimum="1em" space-after.maximum="1.2em" hyphenate="true" white-space-collapse="false" white-space-treatment="preserve" linefeed-treatment="preserve" font-family="DejaVuSansMono" background-color="#FBFEDF" color="black" padding-left="12pt" padding-right="12pt" padding-top="6pt" padding-bottom="6pt" margin-left="0pc">5.times { |i| puts i }</fo:block>
      ist <fo:inline font-family="DejaVuSansMono">i</fo:inline> der Iterator und <fo:inline font-family="DejaVuSansMono">puts i</fo:inline> der
      Block.</fo:block><fo:block space-before.minimum="0.1em" space-before.optimum="0.1em" space-before.maximum="0.1em" space-after.optimum="1em" space-after.minimum="0.8em" space-after.maximum="1.2em">Das ganze kann aber auch in der folgenden Form ausgedrückt
      werden:<fo:block id="id2548272" text-align="start" wrap-option="wrap" hyphenation-character="\" space-before.minimum="0.8em" space-before.optimum="1em" space-before.maximum="1.2em" space-after.minimum="0.8em" space-after.optimum="1em" space-after.maximum="1.2em" hyphenate="true" white-space-collapse="false" white-space-treatment="preserve" linefeed-treatment="preserve" font-family="DejaVuSansMono" background-color="#FBFEDF" color="black" padding-left="12pt" padding-right="12pt" padding-top="6pt" padding-bottom="6pt" margin-left="0pc">5.times do |i|
  puts i
end</fo:block></fo:block><fo:block id="id2548276"><fo:block><fo:block><fo:block margin-left="0pc" font-family="MetaPlusBold,Symbol,ZapfDingbats" keep-together.within-column="always"><fo:block keep-with-next.within-column="always"><fo:block font-family="MetaPlusBold" font-weight="bold" keep-with-next.within-column="always" space-before.minimum="1.8em" space-before.optimum="2.0em" space-before.maximum="2.2em" space-after.minimum="0.1em" space-after.optimum="0.1em" space-after.maximum="0.1em" text-align="left" start-indent="0pc"><fo:block color="#000033" font-size="11.7pt">2.9.2.1. Iterator</fo:block></fo:block></fo:block></fo:block></fo:block></fo:block><fo:block space-before.minimum="0.1em" space-before.optimum="0.1em" space-before.maximum="0.1em" space-after.optimum="1em" space-after.minimum="0.8em" space-after.maximum="1.2em">Iteratoren sind nichts weiter als eine bestimmte Art von
        Methoden. (das englische Wort <fo:inline>„Iterate“</fo:inline> heißt
        <fo:inline>„wiederholen“</fo:inline>.) Bei der Klasse
        <fo:inline font-family="DejaVuSansMono">Fixnum</fo:inline> gibt es zum Beispiel den Iterator
        <fo:inline font-family="DejaVuSansMono">times</fo:inline>. Mal schauen was uns
        ri dazu als Hilfe anbietet:<fo:block id="id2548306" text-align="start" wrap-option="wrap" hyphenation-character="\" space-before.minimum="0.8em" space-before.optimum="1em" space-before.maximum="1.2em" space-after.minimum="0.8em" space-after.optimum="1em" space-after.maximum="1.2em" hyphenate="true" white-space-collapse="false" white-space-treatment="preserve" linefeed-treatment="preserve" font-family="DejaVuSansMono" background-color="#FBFEDF" color="black" padding-left="12pt" padding-right="12pt" padding-top="6pt" padding-bottom="6pt" margin-left="0pc">sw@debian:~/sandbox$ <fo:inline font-weight="bold">ri Fixnum.times</fo:inline>
---------------------------------------------------------- Integer#times
     int.times {|i| block }     =&gt; int

     From Ruby 1.9.1
------------------------------------------------------------------------
     Iterates block _int_ times, passing in values from zero to _int_ -
     1.

        5.times do |i|
          print i, " "
        end

     _produces:_

        0 1 2 3 4

sw@debian:~/sandbox$</fo:block></fo:block><fo:block space-before.minimum="0.1em" space-before.optimum="0.1em" space-before.maximum="0.1em" space-after.optimum="1em" space-after.minimum="0.8em" space-after.maximum="1.2em">Und dort steht auch direkt ein schönes Beispiel, welches wir im
        irb ausprobieren:<fo:block id="id2548328" text-align="start" wrap-option="wrap" hyphenation-character="\" space-before.minimum="0.8em" space-before.optimum="1em" space-before.maximum="1.2em" space-after.minimum="0.8em" space-after.optimum="1em" space-after.maximum="1.2em" hyphenate="true" white-space-collapse="false" white-space-treatment="preserve" linefeed-treatment="preserve" font-family="DejaVuSansMono" background-color="#FBFEDF" color="black" padding-left="12pt" padding-right="12pt" padding-top="6pt" padding-bottom="6pt" margin-left="0pc">sw@debian:~/sandbox$ <fo:inline font-weight="bold">irb</fo:inline>
irb(main):001:0&gt; <fo:inline font-weight="bold">5.times do |i|</fo:inline>
irb(main):002:1* <fo:inline font-weight="bold">puts i</fo:inline>
irb(main):003:1&gt; <fo:inline font-weight="bold">end</fo:inline>
0
1
2
3
4
=&gt; 5
irb(main):004:0&gt; <fo:inline font-weight="bold">exit</fo:inline>
</fo:block></fo:block><fo:block space-before.minimum="0.1em" space-before.optimum="0.1em" space-before.maximum="0.1em" space-after.optimum="1em" space-after.minimum="0.8em" space-after.maximum="1.2em">Und es gibt auch noch eine kurze Schreibweise für kleine
        Blöcke:<fo:block id="id2548355" text-align="start" wrap-option="wrap" hyphenation-character="\" space-before.minimum="0.8em" space-before.optimum="1em" space-before.maximum="1.2em" space-after.minimum="0.8em" space-after.optimum="1em" space-after.maximum="1.2em" hyphenate="true" white-space-collapse="false" white-space-treatment="preserve" linefeed-treatment="preserve" font-family="DejaVuSansMono" background-color="#FBFEDF" color="black" padding-left="12pt" padding-right="12pt" padding-top="6pt" padding-bottom="6pt" margin-left="0pc">sw@debian:~/sandbox$ <fo:inline font-weight="bold">irb</fo:inline>
irb(main):001:0&gt; <fo:inline font-weight="bold">5.times { |i| puts i }</fo:inline>
0
1
2
3
4
=&gt; 5
irb(main):002:0&gt; <fo:inline font-weight="bold">exit</fo:inline>
</fo:block></fo:block><fo:block space-before.minimum="0.1em" space-before.optimum="0.1em" space-before.maximum="0.1em" space-after.optimum="1em" space-after.minimum="0.8em" space-after.maximum="1.2em">Ein Iterator muss übrigens dem Block nicht zwangsläufig eine
        Variable übergeben:<fo:block id="id2548375" text-align="start" wrap-option="wrap" hyphenation-character="\" space-before.minimum="0.8em" space-before.optimum="1em" space-before.maximum="1.2em" space-after.minimum="0.8em" space-after.optimum="1em" space-after.maximum="1.2em" hyphenate="true" white-space-collapse="false" white-space-treatment="preserve" linefeed-treatment="preserve" font-family="DejaVuSansMono" background-color="#FBFEDF" color="black" padding-left="12pt" padding-right="12pt" padding-top="6pt" padding-bottom="6pt" margin-left="0pc">sw@debian:~/sandbox$ <fo:inline font-weight="bold">irb</fo:inline>
irb(main):001:0&gt; <fo:inline font-weight="bold">5.times { puts 'Das blaue Haus.' }</fo:inline>
Das blaue Haus.
Das blaue Haus.
Das blaue Haus.
Das blaue Haus.
Das blaue Haus.
=&gt; 5
irb(main):002:0&gt; <fo:inline font-weight="bold">exit</fo:inline>
</fo:block></fo:block></fo:block><fo:block id="id2548393"><fo:block><fo:block><fo:block margin-left="0pc" font-family="MetaPlusBold,Symbol,ZapfDingbats" keep-together.within-column="always"><fo:block keep-with-next.within-column="always"><fo:block font-family="MetaPlusBold" font-weight="bold" keep-with-next.within-column="always" space-before.minimum="1.8em" space-before.optimum="2.0em" space-before.maximum="2.2em" space-after.minimum="0.1em" space-after.optimum="0.1em" space-after.maximum="0.1em" text-align="left" start-indent="0pc"><fo:block color="#000033" font-size="11.7pt">2.9.2.2. Block</fo:block></fo:block></fo:block></fo:block></fo:block></fo:block><fo:block space-before.minimum="0.1em" space-before.optimum="0.1em" space-before.maximum="0.1em" space-after.optimum="1em" space-after.minimum="0.8em" space-after.maximum="1.2em">Ein Block ist nichts anderes als das von einem Iterator
        ausgelöste Programm. Im Block hat man Zugriff auf die vom Iterator
        übergebene lokale Variable.</fo:block></fo:block><fo:block id="id2548407"><fo:block><fo:block><fo:block margin-left="0pc" font-family="MetaPlusBold,Symbol,ZapfDingbats" keep-together.within-column="always"><fo:block keep-with-next.within-column="always"><fo:block font-family="MetaPlusBold" font-weight="bold" keep-with-next.within-column="always" space-before.minimum="1.8em" space-before.optimum="2.0em" space-before.maximum="2.2em" space-after.minimum="0.1em" space-after.optimum="0.1em" space-after.maximum="0.1em" text-align="left" start-indent="0pc"><fo:block color="#000033" font-size="11.7pt">2.9.2.3. Methode upto</fo:block></fo:block></fo:block></fo:block></fo:block></fo:block><fo:block space-before.minimum="0.1em" space-before.optimum="0.1em" space-before.maximum="0.1em" space-after.optimum="1em" space-after.minimum="0.8em" space-after.maximum="1.2em">Neben <fo:inline font-family="DejaVuSansMono">times</fo:inline> gibt es noch die Methode
        <fo:inline font-family="DejaVuSansMono">upto</fo:inline>, um leicht eine Schleife zu realisieren.
        ri gibt uns auch hier ein schönes Beispiel:<fo:block id="id2548425" text-align="start" wrap-option="wrap" hyphenation-character="\" space-before.minimum="0.8em" space-before.optimum="1em" space-before.maximum="1.2em" space-after.minimum="0.8em" space-after.optimum="1em" space-after.maximum="1.2em" hyphenate="true" white-space-collapse="false" white-space-treatment="preserve" linefeed-treatment="preserve" font-family="DejaVuSansMono" background-color="#FBFEDF" color="black" padding-left="12pt" padding-right="12pt" padding-top="6pt" padding-bottom="6pt" margin-left="0pc">sw@debian:~/sandbox$ <fo:inline font-weight="bold">ri Fixnum.upto</fo:inline>
----------------------------------------------------------- Integer#upto
     int.upto(limit) {|i| block }     =&gt; int

     From Ruby 1.9.1
------------------------------------------------------------------------
     Iterates _block_, passing in integer values from _int_ up to and
     including _limit_.

        5.upto(10) { |i| print i, " " }

     _produces:_

        5 6 7 8 9 10

sw@debian:~/sandbox$ </fo:block></fo:block></fo:block></fo:block></fo:block><fo:block id="ruby-array-und-hash"><fo:block><fo:block><fo:block margin-left="0pc" font-family="MetaPlusBold,Symbol,ZapfDingbats" keep-together.within-column="always"><fo:block keep-with-next.within-column="always"><fo:block font-family="MetaPlusBold" font-weight="bold" keep-with-next.within-column="always" space-before.minimum="1.8em" space-before.optimum="2.0em" space-before.maximum="2.2em" space-after.minimum="0.1em" space-after.optimum="0.1em" space-after.maximum="0.1em" text-align="left" start-indent="0pc"><fo:marker marker-class-name="section.head.marker">Arrays und Hashes</fo:marker><fo:block color="#000033" font-size="14.4pt">2.10. Arrays und Hashes</fo:block></fo:block></fo:block></fo:block></fo:block></fo:block><fo:block space-before.minimum="0.1em" space-before.optimum="0.1em" space-before.maximum="0.1em" space-after.optimum="1em" space-after.minimum="0.8em" space-after.maximum="1.2em">Wie in vielen Programmiersprachen sind auch in Ruby Arrays und
    Hashes beliebte Mechanismen um Daten zu speichern.</fo:block><fo:block id="id2548459"><fo:block><fo:block><fo:block margin-left="0pc" font-family="MetaPlusBold,Symbol,ZapfDingbats" keep-together.within-column="always"><fo:block keep-with-next.within-column="always"><fo:block font-family="MetaPlusBold" font-weight="bold" keep-with-next.within-column="always" space-before.minimum="1.8em" space-before.optimum="2.0em" space-before.maximum="2.2em" space-after.minimum="0.1em" space-after.optimum="0.1em" space-after.maximum="0.1em" text-align="left" start-indent="0pc"><fo:marker marker-class-name="section.head.marker">Array</fo:marker><fo:block color="#000033" font-size="12.6pt">2.10.1. Array</fo:block></fo:block></fo:block></fo:block></fo:block></fo:block><fo:block space-before.minimum="0.1em" space-before.optimum="0.1em" space-before.maximum="0.1em" space-after.optimum="1em" space-after.minimum="0.8em" space-after.maximum="1.2em">Eine Array ist eine Liste von Objekten. Spielen wir doch einmal
      ein wenig im irb.<fo:block id="id2548469" text-align="start" wrap-option="wrap" hyphenation-character="\" space-before.minimum="0.8em" space-before.optimum="1em" space-before.maximum="1.2em" space-after.minimum="0.8em" space-after.optimum="1em" space-after.maximum="1.2em" hyphenate="true" white-space-collapse="false" white-space-treatment="preserve" linefeed-treatment="preserve" font-family="DejaVuSansMono" background-color="#FBFEDF" color="black" padding-left="12pt" padding-right="12pt" padding-top="6pt" padding-bottom="6pt" margin-left="0pc">sw@debian:~/sandbox$ <fo:inline font-weight="bold">irb</fo:inline>
irb(main):001:0&gt; <fo:inline font-weight="bold">a = [1,2,3,4,5]</fo:inline>
=&gt; [1, 2, 3, 4, 5]
irb(main):002:0&gt; <fo:inline font-weight="bold">a.class</fo:inline>
=&gt; Array
irb(main):003:0&gt; <fo:inline font-weight="bold">exit</fo:inline>
</fo:block></fo:block><fo:block space-before.minimum="0.1em" space-before.optimum="0.1em" space-before.maximum="0.1em" space-after.optimum="1em" space-after.minimum="0.8em" space-after.maximum="1.2em">Das ist einfach und verständlich.</fo:block><fo:block space-before.minimum="0.1em" space-before.optimum="0.1em" space-before.maximum="0.1em" space-after.optimum="1em" space-after.minimum="0.8em" space-after.maximum="1.2em">Mal schauen ob das so auch mit Strings im Array
      funktioniert.<fo:block id="id2548496" text-align="start" wrap-option="wrap" hyphenation-character="\" space-before.minimum="0.8em" space-before.optimum="1em" space-before.maximum="1.2em" space-after.minimum="0.8em" space-after.optimum="1em" space-after.maximum="1.2em" hyphenate="true" white-space-collapse="false" white-space-treatment="preserve" linefeed-treatment="preserve" font-family="DejaVuSansMono" background-color="#FBFEDF" color="black" padding-left="12pt" padding-right="12pt" padding-top="6pt" padding-bottom="6pt" margin-left="0pc">sw@debian:~/sandbox$ <fo:inline font-weight="bold">irb</fo:inline>
irb(main):001:0&gt; <fo:inline font-weight="bold">a = ['Test', 'Apfelbaum', 'blau']</fo:inline>
=&gt; ["Test", "Apfelbaum", "blau"]
irb(main):002:0&gt; <fo:inline font-weight="bold">a.class</fo:inline>
=&gt; Array
irb(main):003:0&gt; <fo:inline font-weight="bold">a[1]</fo:inline>
=&gt; "Apfelbaum"
irb(main):004:0&gt; <fo:inline font-weight="bold">a[1].class</fo:inline>
=&gt; String
irb(main):005:0&gt; <fo:inline font-weight="bold">exit</fo:inline>
