        <fo:inline font-family="DejaVuSansMono">each</fo:inline> anzuwenden ist:<fo:block id="id2549017" text-align="start" wrap-option="wrap" hyphenation-character="\" space-before.minimum="0.8em" space-before.optimum="1em" space-before.maximum="1.2em" space-after.minimum="0.8em" space-after.optimum="1em" space-after.maximum="1.2em" hyphenate="true" white-space-collapse="false" white-space-treatment="preserve" linefeed-treatment="preserve" font-family="DejaVuSansMono" background-color="#FBFEDF" color="black" padding-left="12pt" padding-right="12pt" padding-top="6pt" padding-bottom="6pt" margin-left="0pc">sw@debian:~/sandbox$ <fo:inline font-weight="bold">ri Hash.each</fo:inline>
-------------------------------------------------------------- Hash#each
     hsh.each {| key, value | block } -&gt; hsh
     hsh.each_pair {| key, value | block } -&gt; hsh

     From Ruby 1.9.1
------------------------------------------------------------------------
     Calls _block_ once for each key in _hsh_, passing the key-value
     pair as parameters.

        h = { "a" =&gt; 100, "b" =&gt; 200 }
        h.each {|key, value| puts "#{key} is #{value}" }

     _produces:_

        a is 100
        b is 200

